id: shape/observing-agent
title: "observing agent"
kind: shape-primitive
status: v0-seed
updated: 2026-07-03

definition: >
  An observing agent is any human, AI system, team, tool, repo, organization,
  robot, research project, business, or institution that receives information,
  forms an orientation, and may act from an inference.

can_be:
  - human
  - AI agent
  - business
  - organization
  - research project
  - repo
  - robot
  - institution

agent_risk:
  - hidden inference
  - false certainty
  - unbounded action
  - memory drift
  - proof claims without evidence

agent_need:
  - visible signal
  - labeled inference
  - named gap
  - protected boundary
  - bounded move
  - proof condition
  - memory update

boundary:
  - "The agent may orient, but orientation is not authority."
  - "The agent may infer, but inference is not proof."
  - "The agent may suggest a move, but authorization must stay explicit."

proof:
  source:
    - agents/orientation.yawn
    - core/proof-and-boundary.yawn
  status: seed-backed
